# SAMPLE-OUTDIR — template for the build-pdfs output mirror
#
# To use: copy this file to .OUTDIR at the repo top level (or in any directory
# whose subtree you want mirrored elsewhere -- the nearest .OUTDIR above a build
# directory wins). build-pdfs then mirrors every PDF it builds under that
# directory into the base named below, preserving the path relative to the
# .OUTDIR's own directory: a source in REPO/integrals/lectures ships to
# BASE/integrals/lectures. Missing mirror sub-directories are created; the base
# itself must already exist (else build-pdfs warns and builds locally).
#
# Format:
#   - One bare line is the mirror base directory; a leading ~ is expanded.
#   - Optionally add a line reading BOTH to build locally AND copy the PDFs to
#     the mirror, keeping both. Without it the build goes straight to the mirror,
#     with no local copy. (COPY, the songsheets synonym, is NOT recognised here
#     -- build-pdfs deliberately doesn't wire it yet.)
#   - `LABEL: path' lines name extra flat destinations (see below).
#   - Blank lines and #-comment lines (like these) are ignored; the base path and
#     the BOTH keyword may appear in any order.
#
# Named destinations for selected views:
#   A `%! views: ...' magic comment in a source may tag a view with a colon and a
#   label -- e.g. `%! views: solutions, instructor:TA-dir' -- to drop THAT view's
#   PDF, flat, into the directory the matching `LABEL: path' line names here, IN
#   ADDITION to the mirror. The labelled directory must already exist; a missing
#   label or directory warns and skips only that extra copy. `default:LABEL' does
#   the same for the base (student) PDF. This keeps machine-specific paths out of
#   the git-tracked source: the source names a label, this file maps it to a path.
#
# .OUTDIR is meant to be git-ignored, so each machine or checkout can point
# somewhere different (keep SAMPLE-OUTDIR tracked as the reference).
#
# Edit and uncomment the lines you want (drop the leading "# ").

# ~/Documents/2teach/course-COPY
# BOTH
# TA-dir: ~/shared/calc-ta
